  "text": "Continuous bag-of-words representation Recently, word embeddings have revolutionized the construction of text features. In this study, we adopted vectors from a classic word2vec model [CITATION_1] with 300 dimensions which was pre-trained on the Google News corpus. In order to create a feature representation of the whole text, the text is preprocessed (just like for bow representation) and, subsequently, arithmetic mean of vectors corresponding to all text's words is calculated and used as feature representation.",
